class MultiAccountManager:

        with open(session_file, "r", encoding="utf-8") as f:
            raw = json.load(f)

        ëª¨ë“  ê³„ì •ìœ¼ë¡œ target(ìœ ì €id, username ë˜ëŠ” ì±„íŒ… id)ì— ë©”ì‹œì§€/íŒŒì¼ ì „ì†¡

import requests
import json

class WireAccount:
    def __init__(self, token, base_url="https://api.wire.com"):
        self.token = token
        self.base_url = base_url
        self.headers = {
            "Authorization": f"Bearer {self.token}",
            "Content-Type": "application/json"
        }

    def send_message(self, conversation_id, message):
        url = f"{self.base_url}/v1/messages"
        payload = {
            "conversationId": conversation_id,
            "type": "text",
            "text": message
        }
        resp = requests.post(url, headers=self.headers, data=json.dumps(payload))
        if resp.status_code == 200:
            print(f"[Wire] ë©”ì‹œì§€ ì „ì†¡ ì„±ê³µ -> {conversation_id}")
        else:
            print(f"[Wire] ì˜¤ë¥˜: {resp.status_code}, {resp.text}")

    def send_file(self, conversation_id, file_path):
        # Enterprise API íŒŒì¼ ì—…ë¡œë“œëŠ” multipart/form-data ì‚¬ìš©
        url = f"{self.base_url}/v1/files"
        files = {"file": open(file_path, "rb")}
        data = {"conversationId": conversation_id}
        resp = requests.post(url, headers={"Authorization": f"Bearer {self.token}"}, files=files, data=data)
        if resp.status_code == 200:
            print(f"[Wire] íŒŒì¼ ì „ì†¡ ì„±ê³µ -> {conversation_id}")
        else:
            print(f"[Wire] ì˜¤ë¥˜: {resp.status_code}, {resp.text}")

import asyncio
from nio import AsyncClient, LoginResponse

class MatrixAccount:
    def __init__(self, homeserver, user_id, password, device_name="matrix-bot"):
        self.homeserver = homeserver
        self.user_id = user_id
        self.password = password
        self.device_name = device_name
        self.client = AsyncClient(homeserver, user_id)

    async def login(self):
        print(f"[ë¡œê·¸ì¸] {self.user_id}")
        resp = await self.client.login(self.password, device_name=self.device_name)
        if isinstance(resp, LoginResponse):
            print(f"ë¡œê·¸ì¸ ì„±ê³µ: {self.user_id}")
        else:
            print(f"ë¡œê·¸ì¸ ì‹¤íŒ¨: {resp}")

    async def send_message(self, room_id, message):
        print(f"[{self.user_id}] â†’ {room_id}: {message}")
        await self.client.room_send(
            room_id,
            message_type="m.room.message",
            content={
                "msgtype": "m.text",
                "body": message
            }
        )

    async def send_file(self, room_id, file_path):
        print(f"[{self.user_id}] â†’ {room_id}: íŒŒì¼ ì „ì†¡ {file_path}")
        upload_response, _ = await self.client.upload(file_path)
        if hasattr(upload_response, "content_uri"):
            uri = upload_response.content_uri
            await self.client.room_send(
                room_id,
                message_type="m.room.message",
                content={
                    "msgtype": "m.file",
                    "body": file_path.split("/")[-1],
                    "url": uri
                }
            )

    async def listen_messages(self):
        async def callback(room, event):
            if hasattr(event, "body"):
                print(f"[{self.user_id}] ìˆ˜ì‹ : {room.display_name} | {event.body}")

        self.client.add_event_callback(callback, ("m.room.message",))
        await self.client.sync_forever(timeout=30000, full_state=True)

async def main():
    accounts = [
        MatrixAccount("https://matrix-client.matrix.org", "@alice:matrix.org", "alice_password"),
        MatrixAccount("https://matrix-client.matrix.org", "@bob:matrix.org", "bob_password"),
    ]
    # ë¡œê·¸ì¸
    await asyncio.gather(*(a.login() for a in accounts))

    # ë©”ì‹œì§€ ì „ì†¡

    await asyncio.gather(*(a.send_message(test_room, "Matrix í…ŒìŠ¤íŠ¸ ë©”ì‹œì§€") for a in accounts))
    await asyncio.gather(*(a.send_file(test_room, "./test.pdf") for a in accounts))

    # ìˆ˜ì‹  ë£¨í”„ ì‹¤í–‰
    await asyncio.gather(*(a.listen_messages() for a in accounts))

if __name__ == "__main__":
    asyncio.run(main())
